frameDefinitions: An Earner receives Earnings by providing Goods to a Buyer; providing the Goods also generally entails a cost, which may or may not be included in the consideration.
An Agent has access to a finite amount of some Resource and uses it in some way to complete a Purpose.
This frame describes a situation in which an Owner loses his or her Possession.
A Cook applies heat to Food, where the Temperature_setting of the heat and Duration of application may be specified.
An Ingestor consumes food or drink (Ingestibles), which entails putting the Ingestibles in the mouth for delivery to the digestive system.
frameExamples: This reflects the 15 % jump in <t><fex name='Earnings'>earnings</fex></t> over 1994 .
I <t>used</t> half of the bag of dirt to plant the roses.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Earner</fen> is involved in a transaction or set of transactions as the party that receives payment.
<fen>Earnings</fen> are the money given to the <fen>Earner</fen> in a transaction, generally in exchange for <fen>Goods</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
The person who depletes a Resource to achieve some Goal
The exhaustible commodity that the <fen>Agent</fen> has access to.
What the <fen>Agent</fen> is attempting to achieve by using the <fen>Resource</fen>.
The amount of the <fen>Resource</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> uses to achieve the <fen>Purpose</fen>.
A more specific description of how the <fen>Purpose</fen> is achieved by spending the <fen>Resource</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Resource</fen> is used.
The physical location where the <fen>Resource</fen> is used.
The original <fen>Owner</fen> of the <fen>Possession</fen>.
The object that is possessed by the <fen>Owner</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Possession</fen> is lost.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Possession</fen> is lost.
The <fen>Cook</fen> applies heat to the <fen>Food</fen>.
This role identifes the entity that  directly supplies heat to the <fen>Food</fen>.
<fen>Food</fen> is the entity to which heat is applied by the <fen>Cook</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Temperature_setting</fen> of the <fen>Heating_instrument</fen> for the <fen>Food</fen>.
The <fen>Container</fen> holds the <fen>Food</fen> to which heat is applied.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the heat application occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the heat application  occurs.
The <fen>Ingestor</fen> is the person eating or drinking.
The <fen>Ingestibles</fen> are the entities that are being consumed by the <fen>Ingestor</fen>.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
listRoleExamples: She made a lot of money <fex>in Africa</fex> .
Jim browned the roast <fex>in the oven</fex>.
He baked the cookies <fex>at 350 degrees</fex> for 11 minutes.
Boil the potatoes <fex>in a medium-sized pan</fex>.
Jim roasted the chestnuts <fex>in the evening</fex>.
We baked the cake <fex>in the kitchen</fex>.
